<doc id="305790" wikidata="Q4810364" url="?curid=305790" title="Assumption Island day gecko">
<text>Assumption Island day Gecko (Phelsuma abbotti sumptio ) is a subspecies of gecko. It is named for, and only found on, Assumption Island, a small outlying island to the south west of the Seychelles. This gecko It typically reaches the length of 140 mm, lives on palm trees and feeds on insects and fruit.

